def: A genus of Foraminifera, having a porcelanous shell withseveral longitudinal chambers.
A genus of shrubs or small trees of the Flax family, growing intropical countries. E. Coca is the source of cocaine. See Coca.
To chill; to make cold; to cool. [Obs.] Boyle.
Not borrowed; being one's own; native; original.
Having an oblique lateral deformity of the skull.
Filled to excess with blood or other liquid; congested.

The aperture in the iris; the sight, apple, or black of theeye. See the Note under Eye, and Iris. Pin-hole pupil (Med.), thepupil of the eye when so contracted (as it sometimes is in typhus, oropium poisoning) as to resemble a pin hole. Dunglison.
The organ in which pseudova are produced; -- called alsopseudovarium.
Rolled together downward, the tip occupying the center; -- aterm used in reference to foliation or leafing, as in ferns. Gray.
Without, or apparently without, a scutellum; -- said of certaininsects.
A kind of machine blanket or wrapping material used by calicoprinters. Ure. Lapping engine, Lapping machine (Textile Manuf.), Amachine for forming fiber info a lap. See its Lap, 9.
